When a feature affects both mobile and API repositories:

1. BACKEND FIRST (Mordobo/API):
   - Implement endpoint in API/src/routes/
   - Validate with Zod schemas
   - Test with Bruno/Postman
   - Document in API/BRUNO_API_DOCUMENTATION.md
   - Define TypeScript types for request/response

2. SYNCHRONIZE TYPES:
   - Backend defines base types in API responses
   - Frontend creates equivalent types in mobile/services/
   - Create mapping functions if needed (snake_case â†’ camelCase)

3. FRONTEND SECOND (Mordobo/mobile):
   - Create API client function in mobile/services/
   - Implement call to backend endpoint
   - Handle loading and error states
   - Update components that consume the service4. VERIFY:
   - Test end-to-end flow
